aa(lp187
VBut I have some suggestions.
p188
aVHere's my suggestion:
p189
aVIf we want to think of new kinds of arguments,
p190
aVwhat we need to do is think of new kinds of arguers.
p191
aa(lp192
VSo try this:
p193
aVThink of all the roles that people play in arguments.
p194
aVThere's the proponent and the opponent
p195
aVin an adversarial, dialectical argument.
p196
aVThere's the audience in rhetorical arguments.
p197
aVThere's the reasoner in arguments as proofs.
